    "user_reviews": [
      {
        "title": "An Absolute Beast of a GPU",
        "text": "First, keep in mind, this is NOT a consumer grade GPU used for gaming. If you think more dollars spent equals better gaming performance, sure, but price to performance ratio is not worth it for gaming so look elsewhere. I run this mainly for inference and training of AI models including vision and transformers based models for LLMs and image generation. Coming from an A6000, my world of base models I can work witu just opened up because of the 96GB of memory. Amazing card, amazing performance, well worth it if you consider this an investment.",
        "user_name": "Jonathan",
        "source": "bhphotovideo.com",
        "rating": 5,
        "date": "10 months ago",
        "icon": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/shsm/AGYqVK069MKUDukpip5wO98dhaWPQ-9ZwDDEECMo2nkpr9v-AzKkohPCKK1BOwCUWEdweEo4yw=w40-h40-c0x00000000-cc"
      },
      {
        "title": "Best in class",
        "text": "I work on high resolution, high frame rate immersive media (7680x7680@60FPS), and this is the only GPU that can keep up.\n\nUpgrading from an RTX A6000 with 48 GB of VRAM to this PRO 6000 Blackwell reduced my Davinci Resolve render time from 5 1/2 hours to just 1 hour. A good chunk of that is the additional VRAM, I know, but on the same timeline, a single PRO 6000 card outperformed a configuration with DUAL RTX 6000 ADA cards.\n\nIt’s completely changed my interactive workflow as well, allowing me to move through my work as quickly as I can think.\n\nThe PRO 6000 paired with a 96 core Threadripper Pro rendered the same timeline in 10 minutes. So I guess that means my next upgrade will have to be the processor, memory and motherboard (upgrades are a slippery slope, aren’t they?).\n\nThis is the most expensive component in my kit and worth every penny.\n\nB&H packaged this very securely and it was delivered quickly. Thank you!",
        "user_name": "Doug",
        "source": "bhphotovideo.com",
        "rating": 5,
        "date": "10 months ago",
        "icon": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/shsm/AGYqVK2358aKqAaNSFQ5hF6xPlOvn87DN5KnKOx44Q1Mo0shqMt2_PfKLUO_SjSHZsbJyHEQWg=w40-h40-c0x00000000-cc",
        "incentivized": true
      },
      {
        "title": "Industry-leading performance",
        "text": "This is currently the only consumer card with more than 1TB/s of memory bandwidth, enabling actually useful local AI workflows. It comes at a price, but the perfomance is unparalleled.\n\nThis is the smallbox version, meaning there's no retail packaging. That's fine, but the problem (for B&H) is that the smallbox version also provides no protection for the GPU. Apparently, B&H didn't know this, so they put the OEM box into a larger one, and only added cushioning around it. But since there was no protection in the OEM box itself, the GPU fins were damaged (see picture). I need this GPU for work, so a return is out of the question as it does work, but B&H should improve shipping for this article (e.g. using closed cell foam or bubblewrap all the way around the OEM box).",
        "user_name": "Pierre",
        "source": "bhphotovideo.com",
        "rating": 4,
        "date": "a year ago",
        "icon": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/shsm/AGYqVK3nSf6ID2vQBo2gAI3KqvTG2lG5tiyvJG9AfYnVp4gBACYS8efonyWj7ru2MzY3CMwubA=w40-h40-c0x00000000-cc",
